The error message you provided indicates that there is a problem in your `build.gradle` file. Specifically, it seems that there is an issue with the `android` block or its closure.

Please check your `build.gradle` file for any syntax errors or misplaced blocks. Make sure that the `android` block is properly defined and closed. Here's an example of how it should typically look:

```groovy
android {
    // ...
    // Configuration options for the Android build
    // ...
}
```

If you're unable to identify the issue, please provide the content of your `build.gradle` file so that we can assist you further.

apply plugin: "com.android.application"

android {
    compileSdkVersion 33
    buildToolsVersion "33.0.0"

    defaultConfig {
        applicationId "com.receipe_app"
        minSdkVersion 29
        targetSdkVersion 33
        versionCode 1
        versionName "1.0"
    }
    plugins {
        id "com.divpundir.mavlink.generator" version "0.5.0"
    }
    signingConfigs {
        release {
            storeFile file("C:/Users/noura/source/repos/receipe app/my-release-key.jks")
            storePassword "monorfasa"
            keyAlias "my_alias"
            keyPassword "monorfasa"
        }
    }

    compileOptions {
        sourceCompatibility JavaVersion.VERSION_1_8
        targetCompatibility JavaVersion.VERSION_1_8
    }

    buildTypes {
        release {
            minifyEnabled false
            proguardFiles getDefaultProguardFile("proguard-android-optimize.txt"), "proguard-rules.pro"
            signingConfig signingConfigs.release
        }
    }

    flavorDimensions "cpuArch"
    productFlavors {
        arm7 {
            ndk {
                abiFilters "armeabi-v7a"
            }
        }
        arm8 {
            ndk {
                abiFilters "arm64-v8a"
            }
        }
        x86 {
            ndk {
                abiFilters "x86"
            }
        }
        x86_64 {
            ndk {
                abiFilters "x86_64"
            }
        }
        all {
            ndk {
                abiFilters "armeabi-v7a", "arm64-v8a", "x86", "x86_64"
            }
        }
    }
}

dependencies {
    implementation fileTree(dir: "libs", include: ["*.jar"])
}

The issue seems to be related to the placement of the MAVLink plugin declaration within your `build.gradle` file. Currently, you have placed it within the `android` block, which is causing the error.

To fix the issue, move the MAVLink plugin declaration outside the `android` block and place it at the top-level of your `build.gradle` file, like this:

```groovy
plugins {
    id 'com.android.application'
    id 'com.divpundir.mavlink.generator' version '0.5.0'
}

android {
    // Android configuration options
    // ...
}

// Rest of your build.gradle file
// ...
```

After making this change, try running your Gradle build again. It should resolve the error and properly apply the MAVLink plugin.

